"""
Notation:

<c> - Container : 'volume', 'dataset', or 'zvol'.

Commands always available..

Batch/Interactive:

- UFS:
storage create volume <c> ufs [stripe|mirror] [geoms..]

- ZFS:
storage create volume <c> zfs [stripe|mirror|raidz|raidz2|raidz3] [geoms..]
storage create dataset <c> [dataset|zpool]
storage create zvol <c> [dataset|zpool] reservation

Commands available after we've determined that the storage container specified
is valid..

Batch/Interactive:

storage <c> delete
storage <c> owner [recursive] [user|:group|user:group]
storage <c> group [recursive] [group] :
	- alias for 'storage <c> owner [recursive] :group'

storage <container> permissions <mode> :
	- interactive menu will print out user friendly menu

- ZFS:

storage <volume> set acl [unix|windows]

ZFS specific subcommands that need to be designed and implemented:

- dataset
- zvol

"""

class UFS_CLI(storage.cli.Container):
    """A subclass for managing UFS containers."""

class ZFS_CLI(storage.cli.Container):
    """A subclass for managing ZFS containers."""
